|website=Planetyze|language=en|access-date=2017-10-14}}</ref> The shrine is located within [[Sado-Yahiko-Yoneyama Quasi-National Park]] and is on the eastern base of [[Mount Yahiko]],<ref>Japan National Tourism Organization (JNTO), [http://www.jnto.go.jp/eng/location/regional/niigata/yahikosan.html "Mt. Yahiko Area"]; retrieved 2012-10-24.</ref> a 634-meter [[Sacred mountains|sacred mountain]] which forms the ''[[shintai]]'' of the shrine.
